# Linux Integration Standards

## D-Bus
- Service: `org.boloot.Calendar`, path: `/org/boloot/Calendar` on the **system bus**.
- Per-caller UID config: `~/.config/boloot-calendar/config.toml`, fallback `/etc/boloot-calendar/config.toml`.
- Ship introspection XML; map errors to `zbus::fdo::Error::Failed`.
- Emit `SettingsChanged` signal after config updates.
- Validate `BolootConfig` in `set_settings` before save.

## systemd
- System service (`/lib/systemd/system/boloot-calendard.service`); starts before display-manager.
- `Type=dbus` with `BusName=org.boloot.Calendar`; `Restart=always`.
- Auto-enable on package install (deb/rpm postinst).
- Apply hardening: `PrivateTmp`, `ProtectSystem=strict`, `NoNewPrivileges`.

## Freedesktop
- XDG config dir via `dirs::config_dir()` → `boloot-calendar/`; system defaults in `/etc/boloot-calendar/config.toml`.
- Ship `data/system-config/config.toml` as installed example + `/etc` default.
- Notifications: follow Desktop Notifications spec; respect DND.
- Locale hook: `LC_TIME="…@calendar=persian"` in `/etc/profile.d` — require Polkit, not raw root CLI.

## Packaging
- Support deb, Flatpak, RPM, and Arch (PKGBUILD); data files under `/usr/share/boloot-calendar/data`.
- Native packages call `make install-only`; Flatpak uses host-setup for GNOME extension.
